    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When one of your team children within 60 feet rolls a natural 1 on an attack roll against a foe and fails the attack roll, you can take a Reaction to unleash an intimidating string of abuse at how unfair the situation was, that the gods or the universe (or the poor referee if the encounter is a gladiatorial match or otherwise has one) made a bad call, and other such excuses. Roll a Charisma (Intimidation) check against the foe. On a success, your haranguing throws the foe off, and the foe has Disadvantage on all attack rolls for [[/r 1d4 #rounds]]{1d4 rounds}. However, if you also roll a natural 1 on the check, your team child feels so awkward about all the fuss that they have Disadvantage on their next attack roll made within the next 4 rounds.</p>",
